Location:
DubaiPosition Duties/ResponsibilitiesSUMMARY:Bechtel Civil is undergoing a major business transformation to fully implement BIM processes and technologies throughout its business. As part of this initiative the organization seeks a ENGINEERING BIM Functional Lead who will be responsible for the development, adoption and integration of BIM processes into the ENGINEERING Function. The role requires an individual who has a passion and understanding of implementing BIM processes and technologies to revolutionize EPC processes.The role will reside in the ENGINEERING reporting to the Bechtel Civil BIM Lead. The role will participate in the Cross-functional BIM Working Group to collaboratively develop the complete set of BIM Use Cases and BIM work processes which will transform the way Bechtel Civil executes projects.JOB DIMENSIONS:A.
Supervision Received-
Receives operational and functional direction from the Civil BIM Lead-
Objectives are defined and results are subject to supervisory reviewB.
Supervision Exercised-
NoneC. Contacts-
Maintain a strong relationship with colleagues within the Civil BIM Group-
Maintain a strong relationship with members within ENGINEERING to build a understanding of BIM Use Cases needed to support ENGINEERING Function-
Build a strong relationship with the BIM Technical Specialists / SMEs-
Maintains contact with the business development team to contribute to tender packages and RFP responses.ESSENTIAL JOB DUTIES:-
Adoption and integration of BIM processes into the ENGINEERING function-
Development of ENGINEERING BIM Use Cases by participating in Use Case Working Groups-
Participating in other Use Case Working Groups which relate to ENGINEERING-
Contributing to development, by L&D department, of ENGINEERING BIM Use Case training material-
Provide ENGINEERING BIM Use Case training-
Supporting project ENGINEERING teams with BIM Use Case deployment-
Support the Project BIM Manager in developing project BIM Success Stories-
Providing ENGINEERING specific BIM support to Business Development-
Participate in off-project BIM Reviews-
Coordinate with colleagues across GBU’s to bring best practice into the Cross-functional BIM Working Group.JOB KNOWLEDGE:-
EPC (Engineering, Procurement, ENGINEERING) project delivery experience, preferably within the Civil or Structural sector-
Passion and understanding of implementing BIM processes to improve EPC processes.-
Practical experience with implementing BIM processes within the ENGINEERING function preferred-
Practical experience and expertise with use of BIM software within the ENGINEERING function preferred-
Strong written and verbal communication skills, including presentation skills-
Excellent communication and teamwork skills-
Professional approach with certification (BS and MS degrees in the ENGINEERING functional area)-
Ability to take on additional responsibilities, maximise efficiency and manage priorities-
Experience working in a multi-discipline environmentBechtel is among the most respected engineering, procurement, and construction companies in the world.
We stand apart for our ability to get the job done right- no matter how big, how complex or how remote.
The reliability of our performance, the enduring quality of our projects, the strength of our ethics, and the seriousness of our commitment to safety and sustainability are evident in everything we do.
Bechtel delivers for its customers what others can only promise.Build your career as you build some of the most challenging and complex projects in the world today.Bechtel is an affirmative action/equal opportunity employer (AA/EOE).
